An ugly number is a positive integer which does not have a prime factor other than 2, 3, and 5.
Given an integer n, return true if n is an ugly number.

Solution:
class Solution {
public:
    bool isUgly(int n) {
        if(n<=0) return false;
        while(n>1){
            if(n%2==0)n=n/2;
            else if(n%3==0)n=n/3;
            else if(n%5==0)n=n/5;
            else break;
        }
        return n==1;
    }
};

Example 1:
Input: n = 6
Output: true
Explanation: 6 = 2 × 3

Example 2:
Input: n = 1
Output: true
Explanation: 1 has no prime factors.

Example 3:
Input: n = 14
Output: false
Explanation: 14 is not ugly since it includes the prime factor 7.
